
        txtcit.c

        Usage :
                txtcit [ -i infile ] [-o outfile ] [ -sb start_block ]
                       [ -eb end_block ]

        if infile not specified, defaults to stdin
        if outfile not specified, defaults to stdout
        default sb = 0;
        default eb = end of file if sb == 0 else eb == sb +1

        txtcit parses a tlg .txt file with embedded citation information
        and produces a clean ASCII text file with ech betatext line
        preceeded by it's decoded citation.


